    "doi": "10.1037/0278-7393.34.1.219",
    "mechanism": "The feature model encodes items into a feature space where each element occupies a position defined by independent feature values. Retrieval operates by partial match: a cue activates features matching the target, yielding a probability of recall proportional to feature overlap. The model simulates memory trial sequences with stochastic item encoding and probabilistic retrieval. A distributional analysis compares predicted effect-size distributions (phonological similarity effects, word-length effects) across the empirical observations. The model generates both typical effects and occasional reversals (superior accuracy for similar or long items) without explicit strategy shifts, deriving these patterns from the natural variance in feature encoding and partial-match retrieval dynamics.",
